        "tab_dPpDCJ": {
          "type": "tab",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Stories for Schools",
            "content": "<p>This competition is run by Voxblock (Codek Ltd).</p><p>The Stories for Schools competition is designed to award Voxblock mini schools packs to schools across the United Kingdom to support listening and literacy in the classroom.</p><p>Five schools will each receive a Voxblock Mini Pack.</p><p>Each Mini Pack includes:</p><ul><li>5 x Voxblock audiobook players</li><li>10 x Voxblock audiobooks</li><li>Digital Resource Folder</li></ul><p>The total value of each prize package is £410.</p><p>The prize will be delivered directly to the selected school.</p><p>Prizes are non-transferable and cannot be exchanged for cash or alternative products.</p><h3><strong>How to Enter</strong></h3><p>Entries must be submitted via the form found at voxblock.co.uk/pages/worldbookday</p><p>Entrants will be asked to nominate a school and answer a small number of questions explaining why the school would benefit from receiving a Voxblock Mini Pack.</p><p>Entries must follow the instructions provided in the competition advertisement or promotional material.</p><p>Entries submitted through agents or third parties will not be accepted.</p><p>Incomplete, illegible or late entries will not be counted.</p><h5><strong>Eligibility</strong></h5><p>The competition is open to schools of the United Kingdom.</p><p>Entrants may nominate any UK primary school and must be aged 18 or over.</p><p>Multiple nominations may be received for the same school.</p><p>Employees of Voxblock (Codek Ltd) or associated companies are not eligible to enter.</p><h5><strong>Competition Period</strong></h5><p>The competition opens on <strong>Thursday 5th March 2026</strong>.</p><p>The closing date for entries is <strong>26th March 2026</strong>.</p><p>Entries received after this date will not be considered.</p><h3><strong>Selection of Winning Schools</strong></h3><p>Winning schools will be selected by a judging panel organised by Voxblock.</p><p>Judges may include representatives from Voxblock and partner organisations supporting the competition.</p><p>Entries will be reviewed based on the responses provided and the demonstrated benefit the Voxblock Mini Pack would bring to the nominated school.</p><p>Entries are not selected based on how many nominations a school receives. However, schools that receive a higher number of nominations may provide additional context and insight for the judging panel when reviewing submissions.</p><p>Judging criteria for written response questions are:</p><ul><li><em><strong>Q1: Tell us your school's initiatives for championing the Year of Reading</strong></em></li></ul><p>Submissions will be judged on how clearly the school demonstrates a commitment to encouraging reading across the school community. Judges will look for examples of creativity, consistency, and impact in the activities or programmes being delivered.</p><p>Things judges will look for:</p><ul><li><strong>Range of initiatives</strong> – Evidence that reading is promoted through multiple activities or programmes.</li><li><strong>Whole-school involvement</strong> – Participation from pupils, teachers, and potentially families or the wider community.</li><li><strong>Creativity and engagement</strong> – Fun or imaginative ways the school encourages children to read.</li><li><strong>Impact on pupils</strong> – How these initiatives help build confidence, enjoyment, or engagement with reading.</li><li><em><strong>Q2: Tell us about any challenges your school faces in supporting reading and learning</strong></em></li></ul><p>Submissions will be judged on how clearly schools explain the barriers they face in supporting literacy, and how additional resources could help make a difference. Judges will look for honest and thoughtful reflections on the needs of pupils.</p><p>Things judges will look for:</p><ul><li><strong>Clarity of the challenge</strong> – A clear explanation of the barriers affecting reading development.</li><li><strong>Understanding of pupil needs</strong> – Insight into the specific needs of the children in the school.</li><li><strong>Potential impact</strong> – How additional support or resources could help address these challenges.</li><li><strong>Thoughtfulness</strong> – Genuine reflections rather than generic statements.</li></ul><p>The judges’ decision is final and no correspondence will be entered into.</p><h4><strong>Notification of Winners</strong></h4><p>The individuals who nominated the winning schools will be contacted via the email address used to submit their entry.</p><p>If a response is not received within <strong>5 working days</strong>, Voxblock reserves the right to select an alternative winner.</p><p>Once confirmed, Voxblock will coordinate delivery of the prize directly with the relevant school.</p><h5><strong>Data Protection</strong></h5><p>Voxblock will process personal information provided in accordance with its privacy policy and relevant data protection legislation.</p><p>Personal information supplied will only be used to administer the competition and contact entrants regarding their submission.</p><p>Entrants may also receive email communications from Voxblock if they choose to opt in to marketing communications.</p><p>Entrants may unsubscribe from Voxblock emails at any time.</p><h5><strong>Publicity</strong></h5><p>By entering the competition, entrants agree that Voxblock may use the name of the winning school and selected excerpts from the winning nomination for promotional and publicity purposes.</p><p>No additional compensation will be provided for such use.</p><h5><strong>General</strong></h5><p>Voxblock does not accept responsibility for any late, lost or misdirected entries.</p><p>Voxblock reserves the right to:</p><ul><li>cancel the competition</li><li>refuse any entry</li><li>amend these terms and conditions where necessary</li></ul><p>Subject to the maximum extent permitted by law, Voxblock and its associated companies exclude responsibility for any loss, damage or liability arising from participation in the competition or acceptance of the prize.</p>",
